  "properties": {
    "encrypted": "false",
    "long_instructions": "A physician wants a quick way to determine if a patient might be sick based on their body temperature. A person's normal body temperature is 98.6 degrees and shouldn't be more than 0.5 degrees from the norm.\r\n\r\n✅ <strong>TO DO #1:</strong> In <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">Physician.java</code>, write the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">isSick()</code> method. This method should:\r\n\r\n1. Take a <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">Patient</code> object as a parameter.\r\n\r\n2. Use <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">Math.abs()</code> to check whether the patient’s temperature is more than 0.5 degrees away from 98.6.\r\n\r\n3. Return <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">true</code> if the patient is sick, and <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">false</code> otherwise.\r\n\r\n✅ <strong>TO DO #2:</strong> In <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">PhysicianRunner.java</code>, call the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">isSick()</code> method once for each patient and print whether they are sick.\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background-color: #E0D1EC; border: 1px solid #9660bf; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 1.1em; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 10px;\">\r\n💡 <strong>TIP:</strong> Use <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">Math.abs(patient.getTemp() - 98.6)</code> to calculate how far the temperature is from normal.\r\n</div>\r\n",
